[thinking] I'm wondering if the final metadata should focus solely on the library. If I add a test that collects proxy config for Function, it might change the metadata generated. The original task didn’t require metadata, maybe just tests? I'm considering that existing metadata lacks proxies. If native tests need metadata, they might fail. It makes sense that the TCK runs the agent to collect metadata from tests and compare it to the repository. This challenge seems to improve dynamic-access coverage since tests collect dynamic accesses, even if they don’t directly interact with repository metadata.
